	In addition to the accident prevention program activities, the Minnesota Refining Division has safety features on many units to help (1) contain/control a release, (2) quickly detect a release, and (3) reduce the consequences of a release.  The following types of safety features are used in various processes:

Release Detection

(	Hydrocarbon detectors with alarms in the liquefied petroleum gas (LPG) storage and other areas;

(	Hydrofluoric acid detectors with alarms in the HF Alkylation Unit;

Release Containment/Control

* Process relief valves that discharge to a flare to capture and incinerate process materials to prevent overpressure damage to equipment;

* Scrubber to neutralize hydrofluoric acid releases to the flare in the HF Alkylation Unit;

* Manual and automatic valves to permit isolation of equipment or process units;

* Automated shutdown systems for specific process parameters (e.g., high level, high temperature);

* Curbing or diking to contain liquid releases;

* Redundant equipment and instrumentation where needed (e.g., uninterruptible power supply for process control system, redundant firewater pumps);

* Water spray systems;

* Fire suppression and extinguishing systems;

* Trained emergency response personnel;

* Personal protective equipment (e.g., protective clothing, self-contained breathing apparatus);

* Structurally adequate control buildings to help protect control systems and personnel.


